column63: When answering I've imagined the use of AI eg for species ID "embebed" in other Apps or platforms

AI can be used to provide different user experience depending on the profile and learn to adapt the system. AI can provide automatic feedback. flow of data will be reduced as it needs to go to the algorithms and require connection with server and feedback.
Lots of 'it depends' answers to these questions!

column83: Augmented reality can include live identification of things seen through people'e eye, or 3D reconstructions of the landscape as it looked in the past (e.g. before the management action, or before arrival of a certain invasive species), or how it could look following certain management actions (user could select several options). In case of live identification, this would need a large flow of data which would limit its use in the wilderness (due to limited internet access). I am afraid too  that people will use it for a while, but eventually be happy to use conventional targeted identification, as constant flow of information would be disturbing.
